    "description": "SIOS Corporation develops and sells software products and SaaS application services in Japan. It operates through three segments: Products & Services, Consulting & Integration, and Software Sales & Solution. The company provides Software as a Service, a software licensing and distribution model; subscription business model; open-source solutions; and API, a set of protocols that enables different software programs and applications. It also offers Gluegent Gate, a cloud-based management of user IDs; Gluegent Flow, a cloud-based workflow system; Gluegent Apps group scheduler that adds schedule management function to Google calendar; and consulting service for supporting RAG implementation projects. In addition, the company engages in infrastructure construction, operational support, and IT system development business, as well as involved in document management software applications. Further, it provides customer support for OSS products and assist financial institutions; contracted development of enterprise information systems; implementing generative AI solutions; and resells and support OSS products. The company was formerly known as SIOS Technology, Inc. and changed its name to SIOS Corporation in October 2017. SIOS Corporation was incorporated in 1997 and is based in Tokyo, Japan."
